Randy Moss can now add coaching to his lengthy list of football accomplishments. Moss has joined Victory Christian Center High School in Charlotte, N.C., as the football team's associate head coach, according to a report by The Charlotte Observer. Moss' son, Thaddeus, joined the team this season for his junior year after his family moved from the New England area, according to Victory Christian coach Dee Brown. Randy Moss last played in 2012 for the San Francisco 49ers, catching 28 passes for 434 yards and three touchdowns. In 14 NFL seasons with the Minnesota Vikings, Oakland Raiders, New England Patriots, Tennessee Titans and 49ers, Moss tallied 982 receptions for 15,292 yards and 156 touchdowns.